  <mads:note type="source">"C. Balbillus, governor of Egypt in the reign of Nero, A.D. 55. and a
      man of great learning, wrote a work respecting Aegypt and his journeys in that country." from
      Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1 1867, p. 454.</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">"Claudius Balbillus, Tiberius, Praefectus Aegypti AD 55-59; games were
      held in Ephesus after 70 (Βαλβιλλεῖα; Balbilleîa) in his honour. Sen. Q Nat. 4,2,13 praises
      his erudition .....His writings, addressed to a certain Hermogenes, were called Aστρολογούμενα
      (Astrologoúmena)..." from Hübner, Wolfgang (Münster). "Balbillus (Barbillus)." Brill's New
      Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2007. Brill
      Online. Tufts University Library. 08 November 2007 </mads:note>
